25|$|Born in Dadaocheng, Taipei, in 1946, Hsieh was a gymnast in {{high school}} and worked as a food vendor before college. He {{received}} a Bachelor of Laws degree from National Taiwan University. Hsieh then obtained a master's degree and later completed doctoral coursework (all but dissertation) in jurisprudence at Kyoto University in Japan. He was a practicing attorney from 1969 to 1981, serving as <b>a</b> <b>defense</b> <b>attorney</b> in the martial courts following the Kaohsiung Incident of 1980.|$|E
